        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## Oxalic Acid — pKa Values from NIST SRD-46\n\n**Oxalic acid** (Ethanedioic acid, SMILES: `O=C(O)C(=O)O`) is a **diprotic acid** with **two dissociation steps**:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | T (°C) | I (M) |\n|------|-------------|-----|--------|-------|\n| 1st dissociation | H₂L → HL⁻ + H⁺ | **−1.2** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 2nd dissociation | HL⁻ → L²⁻ + H⁺ | **3.8** | 25 | 0.1 |",
